                  <summary>The <title xml:lang="ta">Caraḷipputtakam</title> by <persName xml:lang="ta">Iṟāmacāmiyappa</persName>, that is, <persName xml:lang="sa">Rāmasvāmi</persName>. The work, ("the book on the gamut"), is a musical treatise. The intertitles are names of different types of melody. As noted by Vinson (1867), the first lines give a musical score.</summary>
                  
